# CSS Conventions

## No Inline Styles

Never add `style="..."` attributes to HTML elements. All visual rules belong in `style.css`.

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<div style="color: red; margin-top: 8px;">...</div>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<div class="error-message">...</div>
```

```css
/* style.css */
.error-message {
    color: red;
    margin-top: 8px;
}
```

## CSS Custom Properties

All design tokens are defined in `:root` at the top of `style.css`. Always use them instead of hard-coded values.

| Token | Value | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `--bg-base` | `#000000` | Page background |
| `--bg-elevated` | `#111111` | Cards, panels |
| `--text-primary` | `#ffffff` | Headings, body |
| `--text-muted` | `#888888` | Secondary text |
| `--border-subtle` | `#333333` | Borders at rest |
| `--border-hover` | `#555555` | Borders on hover |
| `--accent-blue` | `#3b82f6` | Primary accent |
| `--accent-purple` | `#8b5cf6` | Secondary accent |
| `--font-ui` | Inter, system-ui | All UI text |
| `--font-mono` | Fira Code, monospace | Code blocks |

## Utility Classes

- `.glass-panel` — frosted glass card (`rgba` background + `backdrop-filter: blur`)
- `.btn`, `.btn-primary`, `.btn-ghost`, `.btn-glow`, `.btn-large` — button variants
- Add new utilities at the end of `style.css`; do not create a separate file

## Responsive Design

Use `min-width` media queries (mobile-first). Breakpoint: `768px`.
